# Bug: a local whose ONLY definition is an embedded assignment inside a condition
# (`if ((var2 = expr) == null) {} else { return var2; }`) was emitted with NO declaration, so it
# rendered undeclared -> `cannot find symbol` at both the assignment and the `return var2`
# (fastjson2 JSONReaderJSONB.readLocalDateTime12/14/16 family, +37 tree errors). Two coupled causes:
#   (1) generatedLocalDeclRe counted `return varN` as a declaration (the keyword `return` matches its
#       type-identifier alternative), so addMissingGeneratedLocalDecls thought varN was declared and
#       skipped it; and
#   (2) even when synthesized, the type defaulted to Object because the RHS is a cross-class call
#       (Helper.parse / DateUtils.parse) whose return type no symbol-free scan can resolve.
# Fix (kill-switch JDEC_RETURN_DECL_FIX_OFF): skip keyword-led matches when collecting declarations,
# and declare a returned-but-undeclared local AS the enclosing method's return type (a returned value
# is assignable to it by JLS 14.17). See TestReturnLocalDeclSynthesisIsLoadBearing.
#
# Seed: synthetic `ReturnDeclSeed.readIt()` returning LocalDateTime via `(v = Helper.parse(...)) == null`.
#
# The returned-but-undeclared local is given a declaration of the method's reference return type.
+/LocalDateTime var\d+ = null;/
